INT. LIGHTHOUSE - NIGHT

Rain hammers the glass. MARA (30s, unslept) climbs the iron stair, a dead radio in one hand.

MARA
Someone answered. Someone down there answered me.

INT. KEEPER'S ROOM - NIGHT

She corners OLD TEO by the stove. He does not look up from the map he is burning.

MARA
You said the island was empty.

TEO
I said nobody living.

EXT. CLIFF PATH - DAWN

Mara follows a wire down the rocks. It disappears into the surf. She hesitates, then wades in.

INT. FLOODED CELLAR - DAY

A room under the tide line. A second radio, still warm. Mara keys it. Static, then breathing.

MARA
I'm coming down.

INT. KEEPER'S ROOM - DAY

Teo blocks the door with his body. For the first time he is afraid of her, not for her.

TEO
Whatever wants you to find it wants you to stay.

EXT. CLIFF PATH - DAY

Mara ties the wire to her wrist. Teo watches from above, choosing not to stop her.

INT. FLOODED CELLAR - NIGHT

The breathing has a face now: a CHILD who is not a child, patient in the dark water.

CHILD
You came. They always send someone who is already drowning.

INT. KEEPER'S ROOM - NIGHT

Teo unburns nothing. He simply lights the lamp and waits, the way you wait for weather.

EXT. LIGHTHOUSE - DAWN

Mara climbs out alone, the wire cut, carrying the dead radio like a stone she has chosen.

MARA
Nobody living. I heard you the first time.
